
# Query the group registry using the _Grouper_ api

This code was contributed by The University Of Chicago.

$Id: README,v 1.6 2004-12-09 20:53:30 blair Exp $

---

## Build

    % cd $GROUPER_BASE/misc/grouperq
    % ant

--

## Run

    % cd $GROUPER_BASE/misc/grouperq
    % export CLASSPATH=.:/path/to/Grouper.jar:/path/to/Grouper-lib.jar:/path/to/grouper/conf/dir
    % java grouperq -h

Query for the default subject's group memberships:

    % java grouperq 

Unless a subject is specified on the command line, grouperq will
default to using the subject configured in Grouper's _member.system_
property when connecting to the groups registry.

Query for a specific subject's group memberships:

    % java grouperq -m <member>

Query for the members of a specific group:

    % java grouperq -g <group name>

--

## Bugs

These are less bugs and more incomplete features:

* Start using _GrouperQuery_ for querying
* Add csv output?
* Add XML output?
* Add ability to query for _all_ types of list values
